I do speak from a knowing standpoint, my sister has raised her four childern alone, while  putting herself thru school, and fighting cancer ( which she beat ).<br>
Granted her family helped her as much as we could, but she still faced all of it alone in her own home, with minimal help to actually care for them. <br>
I asked her opinion of a mother who falls asleep for 2 hours and wakes to find her child missing and then dead in a car from the heat.<br>
Her answer was &quot;What the hell was she doing sleeping?&quot; and I said but hey she thought the child was asleep too, it happens, haven't you ever accidently fallen alseep when the kids were little? Her answer was &quot;F no I haven't! and even if I had they certainly wouldn't have been able to get out of the house and into a car!&quot; Well I tried another tactic. <br>
It was an accident Sis, it can happen and I am sure it has, and maybe we shouldn't cast stones etc.<br>
Her answer was a brief silence, and then she said  very emphatically, &quot;I think since you have children you know this but I will point it out anyway, We are adults, we can take care of ourselves, babies can't! That's why you don't fall asleep, why you don't take your eyes off them, and why you do everything in your power  not to let anything happen to them.  It is horrible what that child went thru, and it's truly sad, and we can stand all day and holler and scream, but it doesn't change the fact that that little girls mother didn't do her moral duty by her own child.&quot;<br>
Well enough said I thought. I will add I hope to god nothing ever does happen to any of the children in my family, but I would know that even if a accident did occur that it would be just that; and accident, because the people I know take the precautions, and then double check those to make sure nothing happens.  BTW her kids are now 13, 11, 8, and 5.<br>
I am sorry and deeply sad about what happened to this child, it seems to be happening more and more everyday...<br>
I will not stand in judgement of this women, although I have my own thoughts about her, but I feel that in the end God will judge her, and I certainly wouldn't want to be in her shoes then.<br>
~ Be Well~<br>
