Yeah.. it actually does dear.  When you make a choice, you consciously decide to do something.  &quot;Taking a Nap&quot; is by nature a choice.  She didn't say, &quot;I accidentally fell asleep&quot;, nor did she say, &quot;I was so exhausted I passed out for two hours&quot;.  She said she &quot;took&quot; a nap.  She consciously decided she should lay down and sleep while her kids were running around awake.  SHE CHOSE TO DO THIS..  that makes her negligent.<br>
